  "text": "Horodecki et al. [CITATION_1] showed that this condition is sufficient for separability in C 2 ⊗ C 2 and C 2 ⊗ C 3 , but not for other tensor products. A density matrix having a positive semidefinite partial transpose is often referred to as the PeresHorodecki condition for separability.",
